00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,128
Hmm?

261
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:37,757
You just arrived at OPP,

262
00:12:37,798 --> 00:12:39,550
sat all alone in your cell,

263
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:40,760
minding your own business,

264
00:12:40,801 --> 00:12:42,762
and suddenly,

265
00:12:42,803 --> 00:12:44,430
out of nowhere...

266
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:48,267
Without a guard in sight,
mind you...

267
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:51,270
There's the killer
of your baby brother

268
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:54,064
just standing there,

269
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:56,108
looking right at you.

270
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:00,654
That's all you need.

271
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:03,783
Right there.

272
00:13:04,784 --> 00:13:06,952
Who's the aggressor here?

273
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:08,120
Hmm?

274
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:13,083
Kofi Jones walked 300 yards

275
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:14,710
from his own cell block

276
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:18,798
and bribed a guard
to get to Carlo.

277
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:22,802
You know, every person has a
right to be safe in their home.

278
00:13:22,843 --> 00:13:24,261
Everyone.

279
00:13:24,303 --> 00:13:26,096
I'd like you
to think about that tonight

280
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:27,473
as you go to bed.

281
00:13:27,515 --> 00:13:29,391
And God forbid

282
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:31,560
you ever wake up
to a known killer

283
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:33,729
standing in the room
you sleep in.

284
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:35,898
But if you do,

285
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:37,483
if you do,

286
00:13:37,525 --> 00:13:39,652
I promise you this:

287
00:13:39,693 --> 00:13:42,279
you won't need a law book

288
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:44,782
to spell out your rights.

289
00:13:48,911 --> 00:13:51,497
We'll take five minutes.

290
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:54,500
Slow, gentle music

291
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:56,168
- Oh. Thank you.
- Here you go. Mm-hmm.

292
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:58,128
Note from the jury.

293
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,841
[paper rustling]

294
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:05,719
Who wrote this?

295
00:14:05,761 --> 00:14:07,012
I found it in this envelope

296
00:14:07,054 --> 00:14:09,306
lying on the table
in the jury room.

297
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:12,184
So it could have been
from any one of the 12?

298
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:14,019
Mm-hmm.

299
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:16,689
[Michael] Tell them I'll answer
it at the end of evidence.

300
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:18,691
[Betty] It's a done deal.

301
00:14:18,732 --> 00:14:21,026
Carlo's going down.

302
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:24,864
[quietly] All right.

303
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,499
Lieutenant Cusack.

304
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:37,167
What about him?

305
00:14:37,209 --> 00:14:39,545
[Lee] Interviewed Kofi
right after Nash and Maxwell

306
00:14:39,587 --> 00:14:41,547
did what they did to him.

307
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:42,715
[Nancy] Huh.

308
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:43,716
They've been busy.

309
00:14:43,757 --> 00:14:45,050
"They"?

310
00:14:45,092 --> 00:14:47,136
Cusack's crew.

311
00:14:48,095 --> 00:14:51,181
Nash and Maxwell
run with Cusack?

312
00:14:51,223 --> 00:14:53,392
Cusack's Baxter-owned.

313
00:14:53,976 --> 00:14:58,731
Are you saying that Jimmy Baxter
had LeBlanc removed?

314
00:14:59,315 --> 00:15:02,735
Well, Judge LeBlanc hates
the Baxter family.

315
00:15:02,776 --> 00:15:04,528
I mean, she's never tried
to hide it.

316
00:15:05,112 --> 00:15:07,907
I mean, there's no judge
that they would want less

317
00:15:07,948 --> 00:15:10,075
presiding over their case.

318
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:13,037
In the middle of the trial?

319
00:15:13,621 --> 00:15:16,081
But how would it look
if something happened to me?

320
00:15:16,123 --> 00:15:19,209
I mean, uh,
they-they-they wouldn't do that.

321
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:22,004
Ask Judge LeBlanc if she agrees.

322
00:15:22,963 --> 00:15:24,882
Well, what evidence
have you got?

323
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:26,175
Lieutenant Cusack.

324
00:15:26,216 --> 00:15:27,551
-His crew...

325
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:31,597
Lieutenant Cusack
is a prosecution witness.

326
00:15:31,639 --> 00:15:34,516
He's going to be testifying
against Carlo Baxter.

327
00:15:34,558 --> 00:15:36,018
So...

328
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,937
what you're saying about him,

329
00:15:37,978 --> 00:15:41,607
uh, it just doesn't make
any sense.

330
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:46,278
Nancy...

331
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:52,826
...there's no public scrutiny
of what is going on in there.

332
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:57,456
So it's very important that
we don't stoop to speculation.

333
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:59,083
I mean,
we've got to be rigorous.

334
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:02,836
We've-we've got to be tough
on ourselves, right?

335
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:05,923
Evidence, evidence, evidence.

336
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:07,508
Right?

337
00:16:07,549 --> 00:16:09,134
[sighs]

338
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:10,970
Yeah.

339
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:12,972
Have you...

340
00:16:13,013 --> 00:16:15,182
been to Fiona McKee with this?

341
00:16:16,183 --> 00:16:17,393
No.

342
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:19,478
Okay.

343
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:24,400
Tense music

344
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:50,009
Place your left hand
on the Bible.

345
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,927
Raise your right hand.

346
00:16:55,139 --> 00:16:57,349
[breathing heavily]

347
00:16:57,391 --> 00:16:58,851
Do you swear to tell the truth,

348
00:16:58,892 --> 00:17:00,245
the whole truth
and nothing but the truth,

349
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:01,395
so help you God?

350
00:17:01,437 --> 00:17:03,147
I do.

351
00:17:03,188 --> 00:17:04,857
You may be seated.

352
00:17:05,858 --> 00:17:08,027
It's easier for me to stand.

353
00:17:08,944 --> 00:17:10,529
That's fine.

354
00:17:19,246 --> 00:17:21,040
You know this man?

355
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:25,836
Yeah.

356
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:28,464
He, uh, jumped me on the street.

357
00:17:28,505 --> 00:17:30,632
January, three years ago.

358
00:17:30,674 --> 00:17:32,468
Why'd he do that?

359
00:17:32,509 --> 00:17:35,304
For being there and being Black.

360
00:17:36,513 --> 00:17:38,390
He broke my spine.

361
00:17:39,391 --> 00:17:40,851
[quietly] Jesus.

362
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:42,895
[Justin]
They fused it, but, uh...

363
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:44,897
it didn't take.

364
00:17:44,938 --> 00:17:47,399
At least not all the way.

365
00:17:47,441 --> 00:17:49,818
That's why
I got no balance left.

366
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,404
- That's why this.
- [cane thumps]

367
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:55,908
[Fiona]
Anything else he do to you?

368
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:01,413
He curb-checked me.

369
00:18:02,039 --> 00:18:05,250
[Fiona] Can you explain
to the jury what that means?

370
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,546
[inhales]

371
00:18:09,588 --> 00:18:11,590
He made me, uh...

372
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:17,304
[exhales]

373
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:18,472
Sorry, I can't.

374
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:19,473
[Fiona] It's okay.

375
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:21,308
You don't have to.

376
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:24,061
Your Honor has
the agreed definition?

377
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:28,482
Yes.

378
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,611
[clears throat] "A form

379
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:35,280
of assault
in which the victim's mouth...

380
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:37,199
Jaw wide open...

381
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:39,618
Is forcefully placed on a curb

382
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:42,204
and the victim's head..."

383
00:18:43,914 --> 00:18:48,210
"...is stomped from behind,

384
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:51,964
causing severe injury or death."

385
00:19:00,013 --> 00:19:01,807
How did that affect you?

386
00:19:04,393 --> 00:19:07,479
I wake up screaming
in the middle of the night.

387
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:11,567
I go to bed getting ready
to wake up screaming.

388
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:15,154
[Fiona] Thank you, Justin.

389
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:25,247
Uh, we'll take five minutes
before cross.

390
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:27,249
Slow, somber music

391
00:19:39,136 --> 00:19:41,763
Mr. James,
thank you for your testimony.

392
00:19:41,805 --> 00:19:43,432
I don't want to keep you
on the stand

393
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:45,184
any longer than is necessary,

394
00:19:45,225 --> 00:19:48,645
and I'm sure Mr. Zander
feels exactly the same way.

395
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:52,482
I can't imagine what it
must be like for you to relive

396
00:19:52,524 --> 00:19:54,860
your experience.

397
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:56,320
[quietly] Jesus. This judge.

398
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:57,779
Talk about pro-prosecution.

399
00:19:57,821 --> 00:19:59,531
[Michael] I do have a question.

400
00:19:59,573 --> 00:20:01,533
You have...

401
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:03,535
scarring from the attack.

402
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:05,370
- Is that true?
- Yes.

403
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:07,289
And from the surgeries?

404
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:08,415
Yes.

405
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:11,043
And they're on your back?

406
00:20:11,084 --> 00:20:13,045
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

407
00:20:13,086 --> 00:20:15,881
And the scar
on the side of your neck...

408
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:17,841
Is-is that also from the attack

409
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:19,718
or the surgeries?

410
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,179
Um, no, it's a...

411
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:24,014
it's a tattoo.

412
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,015
[Michael] Oh.

413
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:26,266
Sorry.

414
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:27,452
I couldn't make it out
from here.

415
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:28,727
My apologies.

416
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:31,438
Mr. Zander, are you ready?

417
00:20:36,276 --> 00:20:37,945
Yes, Your Honor.

418
00:20:43,492 --> 00:20:45,118
May I?

419
00:20:47,246 --> 00:20:49,706
The letter "D."

420
00:20:49,748 --> 00:20:51,458
Are you a member of a gang?

421
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,795
Objection. Justin James
is not the one on trial here.

422
00:20:54,836 --> 00:20:57,506
I will allow this question.

423
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:02,594
"D" for...?

424
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:03,595
Desire.

425
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:05,847
[Zander] Desire.

426
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:09,619
Your Honor, may I have
the witness turn toward the jury

427
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:11,603
- so they can see the tattoo?
- Objection.

428
00:21:12,646 --> 00:21:14,273
[Michael] I think,

429
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:17,526
under the circumstance,
it is a legitimate request.

430
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:19,278
I'll grant it.

431
00:21:23,740 --> 00:21:24,783
[Zander] Desire.

432
00:21:25,409 --> 00:21:29,788
Is that the same gang
that Kofi Jones was a member of?

433
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:31,623
Yeah.

434
00:21:31,665 --> 00:21:34,167
[Zander] I'm guessing that
Carlo Baxter's not very popular

435
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:36,962
with the Desire crew
that you run with

436
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:38,630
and are loyal to.

437
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:40,173
Right?

438
00:21:42,843 --> 00:21:44,177
No further questions,
Your Honor.

439
00:21:44,219 --> 00:21:47,097
[Fiona] Redirect, Your Honor.

440
00:21:48,890 --> 00:21:51,810
Carlo Baxter went to jail
for this vicious assault on you.

441
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:52,811
Right?

442
00:21:52,853 --> 00:21:53,854
Yes, ma'am.

443
00:21:53,895 --> 00:21:55,272
Did he plead guilty?

444
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,481
Uh, no.

445
00:21:56,523 --> 00:21:58,358
There was a trial.

446
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,319
Who represented him?

447
00:22:01,278 --> 00:22:02,404
That guy.

448
00:22:02,446 --> 00:22:03,655
[Fiona] Oh.

449
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:05,282
Did you take the stand?

450
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:06,491
[Justin] Yes.

451
00:22:06,533 --> 00:22:07,826
[Fiona]
Did Carlo take the stand?

452
00:22:07,868 --> 00:22:08,827
Yes.

453
00:22:08,869 --> 00:22:10,078
What did he say?

454
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:11,913
He said that I attacked him

455
00:22:11,955 --> 00:22:13,290
and that he was defending
himself.

456
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:16,251
[Fiona]
Did he call any other witnesses?

457
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:17,753
Yeah.

458
00:22:17,794 --> 00:22:18,920
His mother.

459
00:22:20,213 --> 00:22:21,631
[Fiona] He was convicted

460
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:24,009
of the assault, correct?

461
00:22:24,051 --> 00:22:25,010
Yes.

462
00:22:25,052 --> 00:22:26,845
By a jury?

463
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:28,513
Yes.

464
00:22:28,555 --> 00:22:30,849
So they believed you?

465
00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:33,894
Yeah.

466
00:22:33,935 --> 00:22:35,479
They did.

467
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,522
[Fiona] So it follows
that Carlo and his mother

468
00:22:37,564 --> 00:22:39,358
- were lying under oath.
- Objection.

469
00:22:39,399 --> 00:22:41,693
Speculation about what was
in the mind of the jury.

470
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:44,529
Mr. Baxter, you are a racist,

471
00:22:44,571 --> 00:22:46,198
- a liar and a thug.
- Objection!

472
00:22:46,239 --> 00:22:48,033
Ms. McKee.

473
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:52,037
Her Honor Judge LeBlanc's words

474
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:53,997
on sentencing Carlo Baxter.

475
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:58,752
Objection overruled.

476
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:00,879
[Fiona] Thank you, Mr. James.

477
00:23:21,775 --> 00:23:27,572
[sighs]

478
00:23:29,783 --> 00:23:32,244
low, ominous music

479
00:23:45,173 --> 00:23:47,926
Did you forget where you parked?

480
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:52,305
No.

481
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:54,433
That's what I thought.

482
00:23:57,310 --> 00:24:00,939
- Who are you?
- Detective Costello.

483
00:24:00,981 --> 00:24:03,942
C-O-S-T-E-L-L-O.

484
00:24:05,485 --> 00:24:07,362
[Brendan] C-U-S-A-C-K.

485
00:24:07,404 --> 00:24:08,738
Cusack.

486
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:10,007
[Fiona]
What was Kofi Jones arrested for

487
00:24:10,031 --> 00:24:11,616
on the night of October 10th?

488
00:24:11,658 --> 00:24:13,285
Possession of a stolen vehicle.

489
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:15,370
And were those charges
later upgraded?

490
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:17,414
They were.

491
00:24:17,456 --> 00:24:20,125
Vehicular homicide
for the hit-and-run death

492
00:24:20,167 --> 00:24:22,294
of Rocco Baxter.

493
00:24:22,335 --> 00:24:23,879
Carlo's brother.

494
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,130
[Brendan] That's right.

495
00:24:25,172 --> 00:24:26,965
[Fiona] Thank you, Lieutenant.

496
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:33,138
You saw Kofi Jones
on the day of his arrest?

497
00:24:34,181 --> 00:24:35,807
At the station house, yeah.

498
00:24:35,849 --> 00:24:37,809
- Describe his demeanor.
- Uh, objection.

499
00:24:37,851 --> 00:24:39,829
- It calls for speculation.
- He's a police officer.

500
00:24:39,853 --> 00:24:41,646
Don't you read people
for a living?

501
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:44,608
Facial expressions,
body language and so forth?

502
00:24:44,649 --> 00:24:45,984
Every cop does.

503
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:47,819
It's a crucial part of the job.

504
00:24:47,861 --> 00:24:49,696
Overruled.

505
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:51,716
[Zander] I'm asking you
what you remember of Kofi Jones

506
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,450
on the day of his arrest.

507
00:24:53,492 --> 00:24:55,219
We know he'd just run over
a 17-year-old boy, causing

508
00:24:55,243 --> 00:24:58,038
- catastrophic brain injury.
- [Michael] We-we don't need

509
00:24:58,079 --> 00:24:59,331
to hear the detail.

510
00:24:59,372 --> 00:25:00,999
What, so we get
chapter and verse

511
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:02,876
on the curb stomp,
and you don't allow this?

512
00:25:02,918 --> 00:25:05,504
Will you please get
to your point?

513
00:25:07,088 --> 00:25:09,341
Did he seem torn up about it?

514
00:25:11,092 --> 00:25:13,887
I'm not up here
to speak ill of the dead.

515
00:25:13,929 --> 00:25:16,056
[Zander] You're up there
to tell the truth.

516
00:25:19,017 --> 00:25:21,561
Okay. You really want to know?

517
00:25:23,063 --> 00:25:24,981
He looked like
nothing had happened,

518
00:25:25,023 --> 00:25:28,485
like it was
just another Tuesday.

519
00:25:28,527 --> 00:25:30,362
I mean, when I saw him,

520
00:25:30,403 --> 00:25:32,006
he'd just finished eating
a bacon sandwich.

521
00:25:32,030 --> 00:25:35,700
You'd think, you just killed
a man, then...

522
00:25:35,742 --> 00:25:38,119
suspenseful music

523
00:25:38,161 --> 00:25:40,247
[Zander] No further questions.

524
00:25:53,927 --> 00:25:55,512
[lively chatter]

525
00:25:57,639 --> 00:26:00,183
I am so... so sorry
what's happening in there.

526
00:26:00,225 --> 00:26:02,185
- It's not right.
- All that they're saying

527
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:04,396
about him ain't true.

528
00:26:04,437 --> 00:26:06,356
I can drive you home.

529
00:26:06,398 --> 00:26:10,777
For what? So you can bullshit me
some more on the way?

530
